Taapsee Pannu Defends Her Casting As Older Woman In 'Saand Ki Aankh'


Bollywood actress Taapsee Pannu responded to the criticisms directed at her upcoming film 'Saand Ki Aankh' for casting young actresses in the lead roles to play older women. Taapsee questioned why the same was not asked Nargis Dutt when she acted as Sunil Dutt's mother and to Aamir Khan for playing a younger man in '3 Idiots'.

She and Bhumi Pednekar will essay the roles of shooters who are both over 70 years of age. 'Saand Ki Aankh' tells the story of sisters Prakashi and Chandro Tomar from Uttar Pradesh's Johri, who went on to win over 700 medals when in their 70s.
